Heavy Industries Minister @MBPatil said Karnataka and Thuringia can https://t.co/liiva4AKSy", "id_str": "2062946422518137146", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "possibly_sensitive": false, "possibly_sensitive_editable": true, "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 2, "retweet_count": 5, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "3657633680"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": [{"id_str": "4098851654", "indices": [13, 26], "name": "DK Shivakumar", "screen_name": "DKShivakumar"}, {"id_str": "2885586924", "indices": [237, 245], "name": "M B Patil", "screen_name": "MBPatil"}]}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNjI5NDY0MjI0MDkwNDM5Njk=", "text": "Karnataka CM @DKShivakumar on Friday met a high-level delegation from the German state of Thuringia, led by Minister-President Mario Voigt, to discuss strengthening economic ties and investment opportunities. 

Heavy Industries Minister @MBPatil said Karnataka and Thuringia can collaborate in optics, photonics, semiconductors, biotech, EV manufacturing, renewable energy and advanced manufacturing. Shivakumar highlighted opportunities in technology transfer, innovation, skill exchange and next-generation technologies. Voigt praised Karnataka’s R&D ecosystem, startup network, engineering talent, quantum technology & aerospace infrastructure."}}}, "rest_id": "2062946422518137146", "source": "<a href="http://twitter.com/download/android" rel="nofollow">Twitter for Android</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "2373", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

